    <briefdescription>
<para>Software-based servo driver using millis() for timing. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>This driver implements servo control without using the hardware PWM limitations of the Arduino Servo library. Each instance manages its own timing and inherits from Tickable to integrate with the event loop.</para>
<para><parameterlist kind="templateparam"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>kPin</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Servo signal pin number. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>kMinPulse</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Minimum pulse width in microseconds (default: 1000) </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>kMiddlePulse</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Middle pulse width in microseconds (default: 1500) </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>kMaxPulse</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Maximum pulse width in microseconds (default: 2000) </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
</para>
    </detaileddescription>
